			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2867">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I can identify with Diana Stuart Greene&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1650">On Becoming a Postfertility Woman</a>&rdquo;&nbsp;[August 1995]. I have baby clothes in boxes, and carriers tucked in the attic &mdash; and my youngest is twelve years old. A few years ago I talked my husband out of a vasectomy a half-hour before his appointment. Even though I knew that I didn&rsquo;t <em>really</em> want &mdash; and that we couldn&rsquo;t afford &mdash; another baby, there was something too final about a surgeon&rsquo;s knife. I thought it would cut away my memories of those expectant months and the energy I had carried within me.</p>

<p>But now, with one daughter driving and the other in junior high, the romance of pregnancy is gone, and I&rsquo;m ready for a different kind of energy. Maybe I&rsquo;ll invite my women friends to a postfertility dance and tell them to wear lingerie.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Helen Henry<br>Olympia, Washington</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

